const querySchema = Joi.object({
  name: Joi.string().alphanum().max(50),
  page: Joi.number().integer().min(1).max(1000),
});

app.get('/users', authenticate, (req, res) => {
  const { error, value } = querySchema.validate(req.query);
  if (error) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: error.details[0].message });
  }
  // ... use validated `value`
});
```

---

## 🟡 MEDIUM — No CORS Configuration

The app doesn't configure CORS, which means by default Express will **not** set `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` headers. However, this is a misconfiguration risk — if CORS is added permissively later (`origin: '*'`), it would allow any website to read user data.

